nwRevisionLevel.name: nwRevisionLevel
nwRevisionLevel.description: This shows the current revision level of this mib.

nwIpPingTable.name: nwIpPingTable
nwIpPingTable.description: This table allows outbound ping requests to be generated from the Cabletron device to a specified destination IP address. It is indexed by destination address and source address to allow multiple ping requests by different owner IP addresses.

nwIpPingEntry.name: nwIpPingEntry
nwIpPingEntry.description: An IP Ping Table entry containing objects for a particular ping request.

nwIpPingDestination.name: nwIpPingDestination
nwIpPingDestination.description: The IP address of the host/device to be pinged.

nwIpPingOwner.name: nwIpPingOwner
nwIpPingOwner.description: The IP address of the client which created this ping request. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates the request was made from the local console.

nwIpPingType.name: nwIpPingType
nwIpPingType.description: The administrative control of this ping request entry. This leaf is used to create a ping request entry.

nwIpPingAction.name: nwIpPingAction
nwIpPingAction.description: The action to be performed with this ping entry.

nwIpPingStatus.name: nwIpPingStatus
nwIpPingStatus.description: The results of a ping request. A result of alive(4) means the device is responding.

nwIpTraceRouteTable.name: nwIpTraceRouteTable
nwIpTraceRouteTable.description: This table allows outbound traceroute requests to be generated from the Cabletron device to a specified destination IP address. It is indexed by destination address and source address to allow multiple requests by different owner IP addresses.

nwIpTraceRouteEntry.name: nwIpTraceRouteEntry
nwIpTraceRouteEntry.description: An IP TraceRoute Table entry containing objects for a particular traceroute request.

nwIpTraceRouteDestination.name: nwIpTraceRouteDestination
nwIpTraceRouteDestination.description: The IP address of the host/device to be traced.

nwIpTraceRouteOwner.name: nwIpTraceRouteOwner
nwIpTraceRouteOwner.description: The IP address of the client which created this trace request.

nwIpTraceRouteType.name: nwIpTraceRouteType
nwIpTraceRouteType.description: The administrative control of this trace request entry. This leaf is used to create a traceroute request entry.

nwIpTraceRouteAction.name: nwIpTraceRouteAction
nwIpTraceRouteAction.description: The action to be perfomed with this request.

nwIpTraceRouteStatus.name: nwIpTraceRouteStatus
nwIpTraceRouteStatus.description: The results of a trace request. A result of alive(3) means the end device has responded. Otherwise the next hop count will indicate how many hops were traversed.

nwIpTraceRouteNextHops.name: nwIpTraceRouteNextHops
nwIpTraceRouteNextHops.description: The number of next-hop routers/gateways traversed. This value should be used to read entries in the TraveRouteHop Table.

nwIpTraceRouteHopTable.name: nwIpTraceRouteHopTable
nwIpTraceRouteHopTable.description: This table contains the next-hop Ip Addresses of each hop traversed for a particular TraceRoute request.

nwIpTraceRouteHopEntry.name: nwIpTraceRouteHopEntry
nwIpTraceRouteHopEntry.description: An IP NextHop Table entry containing objects for a particular traceroute request.

nwIpTraceRouteHopDestination.name: nwIpTraceRouteHopDestination
nwIpTraceRouteHopDestination.description: The IP address of the host/device for which this entry exists.

nwIpTraceRouteHopOwner.name: nwIpTraceRouteHopOwner
nwIpTraceRouteHopOwner.description: The IP address of the client for which this entry exists.

nwIpTraceRouteHopNumber.name: nwIpTraceRouteHopNumber
nwIpTraceRouteHopNumber.description: The hop number of this gateway in the table of next-hop routers/gateways traversed. This value indicated how many hops away this router/gateway is.

nwIpTraceRouteHopIp.name: nwIpTraceRouteHopIp
nwIpTraceRouteHopIp.description: The IP address of this next-hop gateway.
